reviews.review_text:
My Favorite Show of the Run 3/29 always gets more attention, but this was always my favorite of the 3 shows...even though I think my recording of 3/29 came out a little better.


Thanks for posting all these here...I should get around to more transfers soon.

Keith

My 1st Show I had to promise my mama that I wouldn't start going to shows until I was older than 18 (think she feared that I would run off) & although I'd been a "head" for many years thanks to my older sister & brother, I saved up for the all 3 of the Nassau shows & boy, it was freeeekin' awesome.  I was sort of bummed by all the fuzz on horseback being all militant & scary, but the worst part was at how filthy the parking lot was left after everyone left for the night.  I remember being blown away by how damned friendly everybody was & the music selection for the night made for a deeeeeelightful first for me.  I boogied, I spun, & I was in girlie hebben when the cute guys all wanted to dance with me.  Fun time, fun music, good time, good music.
PS: So far Keith, you put forth the best recordings for d/l, thanksh for the effort & hard work!
